<div class="sectionheader">
    <h2>Join the Stack Exchange team!</h2>
</div>
<div class="sectionbody">
    <div class="sectionbody-main">
        <p>
            In April, 2010, the original Stack Exchange team got together to figure out a mission for the company. Here's what we came up with:
        </p>
        <blockquote>
            Make the Internet a better place to get expert answers to your questions.
        </blockquote>
        <p>
            We've already done that for programming questions (with Stack Overflow), but there are a million other fields that need a similar community
            and we're on track to build them all. We've already got amazing sites for computer <a href="http://stackoverflow.com">programmers</a>,
            <a href="http://serverfault.com">system administrators</a>, <a href="http://gaming.stackexchange.com">video gamers</a>,
            <a href="http://math.stackexchange.com">mathematicians</a>, <a href="http://photo.stackexchange.com">photographers</a> and tons of others.
            We even help people <a href="http://careers.stackoverflow.com">find amazing new jobs</a>, backed by the credibility that they've built up on
            our system.
        </p>
        <p>
            We've done some amazing work, but we need your help to keep growing and reach all our goals.
        </p>
        <p>
            Of course, even the greatest mission can suck if you don't have a fun place to work on it. Fortunately, we've already solved that problem too.
            Not only do we have an amazingly talented team, free lunches and top-notch benefits, but our CEO, Joel Spolsky, has literally written
            <a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/1590598385/?tag=stackoverfl08-20">the book</a> on how to make great workplaces for building amazing software.
            We have the best working conditions and benefits of any startup in New York. We have the <a href="http://www.unionsquareventures.com">best investors</a>
            in New York. And we're building the best Q&A site on the Internet, bar none: a network where experts help each other with their problems, without a
            single teenager discussing, <a href="http://knowyourmeme.com/memes/how-is-babby-formed">um</a>, reproductive sciences.
        </p>
        
